00:50:35.177 --> 00:50:38.764 line:90% position:50% align:center
Until then, what must we do?

00:50:38.764 --> 00:50:41.642 line:90% position:50% align:center
Stay in the Shepherd’s warm embrace.

00:50:41.851 --> 00:50:46.856 line:90% position:50% align:center
In his arms, he protects us from dangers,
small and large.

00:50:46.856 --> 00:50:48.691 line:90% position:50% align:center
In his pastures,

00:50:48.691 --> 00:50:51.861 line:90% position:50% align:center
he feeds us nourishing spiritual food

00:50:51.861 --> 00:50:54.739 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that we have the strength to make a stand.

00:50:55.197 --> 00:50:58.451 line:90% position:50% align:center
With his hand,
he gives generously

00:50:58.451 --> 00:51:00.620 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that we lack nothing good.

00:51:01.787 --> 00:51:05.583 line:90% position:50% align:center
Before we conclude,
let’s visit Liechtenstein,

00:51:05.583 --> 00:51:09.378 line:90% position:50% align:center
located between Switzerland and Austria.

00:51:09.378 --> 00:51:13.049 line:90% position:50% align:center
It may be long in name,
but it’s small in size.

00:51:13.841 --> 00:51:16.552 line:90% position:50% align:center
As the sixth smallest country in the world,

00:51:16.552 --> 00:51:20.222 line:90% position:50% align:center
it has a population
of just over 39,000 people.

00:51:21.515 --> 00:51:26.020 line:90% position:50% align:center
Despite being flanked
by snowy mountains on the east and south,

00:51:26.020 --> 00:51:29.774 line:90% position:50% align:center
the cities in the valleys below
enjoy a comfortable climate

00:51:29.774 --> 00:51:32.944 line:90% position:50% align:center
because of the warm air called foehn winds

00:51:32.944 --> 00:51:35.279 line:90% position:50% align:center
flowing downward from the summits.

00:51:36.447 --> 00:51:39.533 line:90% position:50% align:center
If you’re interested
in trekking the rugged terrain,

00:51:39.533 --> 00:51:42.078 line:90% position:50% align:center
be sure to have a hearty meal beforehand.

00:51:42.078 --> 00:51:44.121 line:90% position:50% align:center
You can try ribel,

00:51:44.121 --> 00:51:47.708 line:90% position:50% align:center
a traditional dish made with cornmeal

00:51:47.708 --> 00:51:51.629 line:90% position:50% align:center
and served with applesauce,
making it a filling and hearty snack.

00:51:51.629 --> 00:51:53.798 line:90% position:50% align:center
The 95 publishers here

00:51:53.798 --> 00:51:58.803 line:90% position:50% align:center
trek the country and dispense
nourishing spiritual food along the way,

00:51:58.803 --> 00:52:03.015 line:90% position:50% align:center
and they also make a small journey
to Switzerland for their meetings.

00:52:03.015 --> 00:52:06.227 line:90% position:50% align:center
The closest Kingdom Hall
is right along the border.

00:52:06.227 --> 00:52:08.270 line:90% position:50% align:center
Although most of the population

00:52:08.270 --> 00:52:11.732 line:90% position:50% align:center
is Roman Catholic,
our brothers still average

00:52:11.732 --> 00:52:13.609 line:90% position:50% align:center
26 Bible studies.

00:52:13.609 --> 00:52:16.821 line:90% position:50% align:center
But the path to preaching
has not always been smooth.

00:52:17.697 --> 00:52:19.782 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our history of preaching is full

00:52:19.782 --> 00:52:21.659 line:90% position:50% align:center
of uphill battles.

00:52:21.659 --> 00:52:24.620 line:90% position:50% align:center
Starting in the 1920’s, the government 

00:52:24.620 --> 00:52:28.249 line:90% position:50% align:center
would try to arrest
anyone distributing our literature,

00:52:28.249 --> 00:52:30.167 line:90% position:50% align:center
whether it was
from house to house

00:52:30.167 --> 00:52:32.420 line:90% position:50% align:center
or even by letter.

00:52:32.420 --> 00:52:36.257 line:90% position:50% align:center
At one point,
all the publishers preaching in the country

00:52:36.257 --> 00:52:38.801 line:90% position:50% align:center
were arrested and detained on a bus.

00:52:38.801 --> 00:52:40.720 line:90% position:50% align:center
What did they do?

00:52:40.720 --> 00:52:43.222 line:90% position:50% align:center
They sang out to Jehovah!

00:52:43.222 --> 00:52:46.308 line:90% position:50% align:center
Undeterred and with dictators rising

00:52:46.308 --> 00:52:48.185 line:90% position:50% align:center
to power in the 1930’s,

00:52:48.185 --> 00:52:52.523 line:90% position:50% align:center
they courageously used the pamphlet
<i>Fascism or Freedom.</i>

00:52:53.232 --> 00:52:55.359 line:90% position:50% align:center
Though persecution was rampant,

00:52:55.359 --> 00:52:57.570 line:90% position:50% align:center
they were unstoppable.

00:52:57.570 --> 00:53:01.157 line:90% position:50% align:center
Like the warm winds
blowing in from the mountains,

00:53:01.157 --> 00:53:03.993 line:90% position:50% align:center
the love of our brothers and sisters
can be felt everywhere.

00:53:04.952 --> 00:53:07.496 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s seen
in their regular Family Worship evenings,

00:53:08.080 --> 00:53:10.458 line:90% position:50% align:center
before and after the meetings,

00:53:10.458 --> 00:53:13.169 line:90% position:50% align:center
and in their singing to Jehovah.

00:53:13.169 --> 00:53:17.423 line:90% position:50% align:center
And they wish to send that love to you,
the worldwide brotherhood.

00:53:18.466 --> 00:53:21.052 line:90% position:50% align:center
From the World Headquarters
of Jehovah’s Witnesses,

00:53:21.052 --> 00:53:23.429 line:90% position:50% align:center
this is JW Broadcasting.

